    S:gt.blockmachines.htgr.name=High Temperature Gas-cooled Reactor
    S:gt.blockmachines.htgr.tooltip=Machine Type: §eBreeder Reactor, HTGR§r\nUses up to §c0.14§7% of fuel per operation, §c10§7% of this value is flat and §c90§7% dependent on the formula y=1-(1-x)^3 (x is % fill level)\nMaintenance problems decrease the efficiency of cooling by §c20§7% for each issue\nUses §c1,536§7 EU/t increasing by up to §c40§7 times when lacking Helium Gas\nHelium gas increases effectiveness of heat exchangers linearly up to §c100§7% at max capacity\nThe Reactor loses §c0.05§7% helium per operation and requires at least §c10§7% helium to start operation\nOne Operation takes longer based on reactor fill level (between §c100§7s and §c1,000§7s)\nProviding coolant/water/both speeds up recipe by §c7§7%/§c3§7%/§c10§7% total recipe time/second\nThe amount of necessary fluid for maximum bonus speed scales with pellets, §c0.5§7 coolant/tick/pellet and §c0.1§7 distilled water/tick/pellet\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§4§lk§c§lu§6§lb§e§la§2§l6§a§l0§b§l0§3§l0§r§7 & §a§1§lPxx500§r§7
