    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.exotic_module.name=Heliofusion Exoticizer
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.exotic_module.tooltip=Machine Type: §eExotic Matter Producer§r\nThis is a module of the Godforge\nMust be part of a Godforge to function\nUsed for ultra high temperature matter degeneration\n§b§m---------------------------------------------------------------------------\nThe fourth and final module of the Godforge, this module breaks apart the very\nbuilding blocks of matter, producing exotic mixtures in the process. Quark-Gluon Plasma\ncan be manufactured right away, but production of Magnetic Monopole Matter (Magmatter)\nrequires a fully upgraded Godforge\nThis module is specialized towards acquisition of unique materials\n§b§m---------------------------------------------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.exotic_module.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §67§7x§67§7x§613§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n   §620§7 Singularity Reinforced Stellar Shielding Casing\n   §620§7 Boundless Gravitationally Severed Structure Casing\n   §65§7 Harmonic Phonon Transmission Conduit\n   §65§7 Celestial Matter Guidance Casing\n   §61§7 Stellar Energy Siphon Casing\n   Requires §61§7 Output Hatch\n   Requires §61§7 Output Bus\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.eye_of_harmony.name=Eye of Harmony
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.eye_of_harmony.tooltip=Machine Type: §eSpacetime Manipulator, EOH§r\nCreates a pocket of spacetime that is bigger on the inside using transdimensional\nengineering. Certified Time Lord regulation compliant. This multi uses too much EU\nto be handled with conventional means. All EU requirements are handled directly by\nyour wireless EU network\n§6§m---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nThis multiblock will constantly consume hydrogen and helium when it is not running a\nrecipe once per second. It will store this internally, you can see the totals by\nusing a scanner. This multi also has three tiered blocks with §c9§7 tiers\neach. They are as follows and have the associated effects on the multi:\n§9Spacetime Compression Field Generator:\n- The tier of this block determines what recipes can be run. If the multiblocks\n  spacetime compression field block exceeds the requirements of the recipe it\n  will decrease the processing time by §c3%§7 per tier over the requirement (multiplicative)\n§9Time Dilation Field Generator:\n- Decreases the time required for a recipe by §c50%§7 per tier of block (multiplicative)\n  Decreases the probability of a recipe succeeding by §c9.25%§7 per tier (additive)\n§9Stabilisation Field Generator:\n- Increases the probability of a recipe succeeding by §c5%§7 per tier (additive)\n  Decreases the yield of a recipe by §c5%§7 per tier (additive). \n  > Low tier stabilisation field generators have a power output penalty\n     The power output penalty for using Crude Stabilisation Field Generators is §c40%\n     This penalty decreases by §c5%§7 per tier (additive)\n§6§m---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nGoing over a recipe requirement on hydrogen or helium has a penalty on yield and recipe chance\nAll stored hydrogen and helium is consumed during a craft. The associated formulas are:\n§aOverflow ratio = (Stored fluid / Recipe requirement) - 1\n§aAdjustment value = 1 - exp(-(30 * Overflow ratio)^2)\nThe Adjustment value is then subtracted from the total yield and recipe chance\n§6§m---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nIt should be noted that base recipe chance is determined per recipe and yield always starts\nat 1 and subtracts depending on penalties. All fluid/item outputs are multiplied by the\nyield. Failure fluid is exempt\n§6§m---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nThis multiblock can only output to ME output buses/hatches\n§6§m---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nThis multiblock can be overclocked by placing a programmed circuit into the input bus\nE.g. A circuit of 2 will provide 2 OCs, 16x EU input and 0.25x the time. EU output is unaffected\nAll outputs are equal. All item and fluid output chances & amounts per recipe are unaffected\n§6§m---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nIf a recipe fails the EOH will output §aSuccess chance * 14,400 * (2.0)^(Recipe tier)§7L of molten\nSpaceTime instead of fluid/item outputs and output as much EU as a successful recipe\n§6§m---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nThis multiblock can perform parallel processing by placing Astral Array Fabricators into the input bus\nThey are stored internally and can be retrieved via right-clicking the controller with a wire cutter\nThe maximum amount of stored Astral Arrays is 8,637. Parallel amount is calculated via these formulas:\n§aParallel exponent = floor(log(8 * Astral Array amount) / log(1.7))\n§aParallel = 2^(Parallel exponent)\nIf the EOH is running parallel recipes, the power calculation changes\nThe power needed for parallel processing is calculated as follows:\n§atotal EU = ((EU output - EU input * 1.63) / 20.7) * 2.3^(Parallel exponent)\nFurthermore, if parallel recipes are run, the recipes consume Condensed Raw Stellar Plasma Mixture\ninstead of helium and hydrogen. Overflow penalties still apply\nThe required amount of fluid to start a recipe is §a12.4 / 10^6 * Helium amount * Parallel\nThe success or failure of each parallel is determined independently\n§6§m---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nAnimations can be disabled by using a screwdriver on the multiblock\nPlanet block can be inserted directly by right-clicking the controller with planet block\n§6§m---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§4§l§o§nC§6§l§o§no§a§l§o§nl§3§l§o§ne§5§l§o§nn§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.eye_of_harmony.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §633§7x§633§7x§633§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n   §6896§7 Reinforced Spatial Structure Casing.\n   §6534§7 Reinforced Temporal Structure Casing.\n   §631§7 Infinite SpaceTime Energy Boundary Casing.\n   §6168§7 Time Dilation Field Generator.\n   §648§7 Stabilisation Field Generator.\n   §6138§7 Spacetime Compression Field Generator.\n   §7§m------------------------------\n   Requires §62§7 input hatches.\n   Requires §61§7 ME output hatch.\n   Requires §61§7 input bus.\n   Requires §61§7 ME output bus.\n   Uses sub channel §6stabilisation§r§7 for §6Stabilisation Field Generator Tier\n   Uses sub channel §6time_dilation§r§7 for §6Time Dilation Field Generator Tier\n   Uses sub channel §6spacetime_compression§r§7 for §6Spacetime Compression Field Generator Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.forge_of_gods.name=Forge of the Gods
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.forge_of_gods.tooltip=Machine Type: §eStellar Forge§r\n§oAlso known as Godforge or Gorge for short\n§b§m-------------------------------------------------------------------------\nA massive structure harnessing the thermal, gravitational and\nkinetic energy of a stabilised neutron star for material processing\nThis multiblock can house §cup to 16 modules §7which utilize the star to energize materials\nto varying degrees, ranging from regular smelting to matter degeneration\nEU requirements for all modules are handled via wireless energy directly\n§b§m-------------------------------------------------------------------------\nThis multiblock has an §6extensive upgrade tree §7which influences all of its functions,\nsuch as §6unlocking new module types§7, §6increasing heat levels §7and §6granting\n§6various processing speed bonuses§7. §7These upgrades can be unlocked by reaching\ncertain milestones and/or spending materials\n§b§m-------------------------------------------------------------------------\n§aClicking on the logo in the controller gui opens an extensive information window§7,\nexplaining everything there is to know about this multiblock\n§b§m-------------------------------------------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.forge_of_gods.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §6127§7x§629§7x§6186§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n   Total blocks needed for the structure with §51§7/§22§7/§b3§7 rings:\n   §53943§7/§27279§7/§b11005§7 Transcendentally Amplified Magnetic Confinement Casing\n   §52818§7/§24831§7/§b6567§7 Singularity Reinforced Stellar Shielding Casing\n   §5272§7/§2512§7/§b824§7 Celestial Matter Guidance Casing\n   §5130§7/§2144§7/§b158§7 Boundless Gravitationally Severed Structure Casing\n   §59§7/§254§7/§b155§7 Spatially Transcendent Gravitational Lens Block\n   §5345§7/§2357§7/§b397§7 §5Remote§7/§2Medial§7/§bCentral§7 Graviton Flow Modulator\n   §636§7 Stellar Energy Siphon Casing\n   §7§m------------------------------\n   Requires §61§7 Input Hatch\n   Requires §61§7 Output Bus (ME)\n   Requires §61§7 Input Bus\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.infuser.tooltip=Machine Type: §eRestorer§r\nSimultaneously recharges and repairs equipment\nStocking input buses are not supported\n§6Recharging§7: No max speed or energy loss\n§6Repairing§7: Max 1k durability/t, consumes 1k EU + 1L UUM per point\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
