    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.molten_module.name=Helioflux Melting Core
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.molten_module.tooltip=Machine Type: §eBlast Smelter§r\nThis is a module of the Godforge\nMust be part of a Godforge to function\nUsed for high temperature material liquefaction\n§b§m--------------------------------------------------------------------------\nThe second module of the Godforge, this module melts materials directly into\ntheir liquid form. If an output material does not have a liquid form, it will be output\nas a regular solid instead\nThis module is specialized towards parallel processing\n§b§m--------------------------------------------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.molten_module.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §67§7x§67§7x§613§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n   §620§7 Singularity Reinforced Stellar Shielding Casing\n   §620§7 Boundless Gravitationally Severed Structure Casing\n   §65§7 Harmonic Phonon Transmission Conduit\n   §65§7 Celestial Matter Guidance Casing\n   §61§7 Stellar Energy Siphon Casing\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.plasma_module.name=Heliothermal Plasma Fabricator
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.plasma_module.tooltip=Machine Type: §ePlasma Fabricator§r\nThis is a module of the Godforge\nMust be part of a Godforge to function\nUsed for extreme temperature matter ionization\n§b§m--------------------------------------------------------------------------\nThe third module of the Godforge, this module infuses materials with extreme amounts\nof heat, ionizing and turning them into plasma directly. Not all plasmas can be produced\nright away, some of them require certain upgrades to be unlocked\nThis module is specialized towards energy and overclock efficiency\n§b§m--------------------------------------------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.plasma_module.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §67§7x§67§7x§613§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n   §620§7 Singularity Reinforced Stellar Shielding Casing\n   §620§7 Boundless Gravitationally Severed Structure Casing\n   §65§7 Harmonic Phonon Transmission Conduit\n   §65§7 Celestial Matter Guidance Casing\n   §61§7 Stellar Energy Siphon Casing\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.research.name=Research Station
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.research.tooltip=Machine Type: §eResearch Station, Scanner§r\nUsed to scan Data Sticks for Assembly Line Recipes\nNeeds to be fed with computation to work\nDoes not consume the item until the Data Stick is written\nUse screwdriver to change mode\nComputation required in scanner mode follows the formula:\nRecipe duration in ticks * (2 ^ (Recipe voltage tier - 1))\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.research.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §63§7x§67§7x§67§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center on the frontside of the main body\n§f   Object Holder: §7Center of the front pillar\n§f   Data Connector: §7Any Computer Casing on the backside of the main body\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any Computer Casing on the backside of the main body\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any Computer Casing with hint number 1 or 3\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any Computer Casing with hint number 1 or 3\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any Computer Casing with hint number 1 or 3\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.smelting_module.name=Helioflare Power Forge
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.smelting_module.tooltip=Machine Type: §eBlast Furnace, Furnace§r\nThis is a module of the Godforge\nMust be part of a Godforge to function\nUsed for basic smelting operations at various temperatures\n§b§m--------------------------------------------------------------------------\nAs the first of the Godforge modules, this module performs the most basic\nthermal processing, namely smelting materials identically to a furnace or blast furnace\nThe desired method of processing can be selected in the gui\nThis module is specialized towards speed and high heat levels\n§b§m--------------------------------------------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.smelting_module.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §67§7x§67§7x§613§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n   §620§7 Singularity Reinforced Stellar Shielding Casing\n   §620§7 Boundless Gravitationally Severed Structure Casing\n   §65§7 Hypogen Coil Block\n   §65§7 Celestial Matter Guidance Casing\n   §61§7 Stellar Energy Siphon Casing\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.switch.adv.tooltip=Machine Type: §eComputation Network Switch, CNS§r\nVariable-length version of the Weighted Network Switch.\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nConsumes §b524,288§7 EU/t per middle slice while active.\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nComputation output is configured by right clicking transmission connectors with a screwdriver.\nTransmission connectors must be part of the structure for them to be configurable.\nComputation output for a hatch is directly controlled by the hatch's setting.\nFor weighted computation distribution, use the §6Weighted Network Switch With QoS§r.\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.switch.adv.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §63§7x§63§7x§63-18§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   0x§7 - §680x §r§7Computer Casing\n§6   1x§7 - §681x §r§7Advanced Computer Casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any Computer Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Dynamo Hatch: §7Any Computer Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Multi-Amp Energy Hatch: §7Any Computer Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Laser Target Hatch: §7Any Computer Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Multi-Amp Dynamo Hatch: §7Any Computer Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Laser Source Hatch: §7Any Computer Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Data Reception Connector: §7Any Advanced Computer Casing (Hint: 2)\n§f   Data Transmission Connector: §7Any Computer Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Data Transmission Connector: §7Any Advanced Computer Casing (Hint: 2)\n   Uses sub channel §6length§r§7 for §6middle slice count\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.switch.tooltip=Machine Type: §eComputation Network Switch, CNS§r\nDistributes computation to transmission connectors based on weights.\nTransmission connectors are assigned an ID.\nScan connectors with a Portable Scanner to determine their ID.\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nComputation output is configured via TecTech parameters.\nThe first parameter in each group controls the hatch ID.\nThe second parameter in each group controls the hatch weight.\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.switch.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §63§7x§63§7x§63§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   0x§7 - §620x §r§7Computer Casing\n§6   0x§7 - §66x §r§7Advanced Computer Casing\n§f   Data Reception Connector: §7Any Advanced Computer Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Data Transmission Connector: §7Any Computer Casing (Hint: 1, 2)\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any Computer Casing (Hint: 1, 2)\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any Computer Casing (Hint: 1, 2)\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.transformer.tooltip=Machine Type: §eActive Transformer, AT§r\nCan transform to and from any voltage\nOnly 0.004% power loss, HAYO!\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.transformer.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §63§7x§63§7x§63§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   5x §r§7High Power Casing (minimum)\n§f   Superconducting Coil Block: §7Center\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any High Power Casing\n§f   Dynamo Hatch: §7Any High Power Casing\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.engraver.name=Hyper-Intensity Laser Engraver
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.engraver.tooltip=Machine Type: §eLaser Engraver, HILE§r\n§a350%§7 Speed\n§b80%§7 EU Usage\nLaser source hatch determines maximum recipe tier and parallels\nRecipe tier and overclocks limited to laser source tier + 1\nWhen using a UEV+ laser source, one multi-amp energy hatch is allowed instead of regular energy hatches\nParallels equal to the cube root of laser source amperage input\nGlass tier determines maximum laser source tier\n§c§l§nUMV§7-tier glass accepts all laser source hatches\nUse screwdriver to disable laser rendering\nUse wire cutter to toggle realism mode if you hate angled lasers\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.engraver.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §65§7x§65§7x§65§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   35x §r§7Laser Containment Casing (minimum)\n§6   9x §r§7Tungstensteel Frame Box\n§6   3x §r§7Any Tiered Glass (tiered)\n§f   Laser Resistant Plate: §7x1\n§f   Laser Source Hatch: §7x1\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any Casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any Casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any Casing\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Any Casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any Casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any Casing\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.entitycrusher.name=Extreme Entity Crusher
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.entitycrusher.tooltip=Machine Type: §ePowered Spawner, EEC§r\nSpawns and kills monsters for you!\nProduces §a120 Liquid XP§7 per operation\nPowered Spawner goes in Controller Slot\nBase energy usage: §b1920§7 EU/t\nSupports §dperfect OC!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHas a minimum recipe time of 20 ticks, further overclocks multiply outputs by 4x\nRecipe time is based on mob health\nYou can additionally put a weapon inside the GUI\nIt will speed up the process and apply the looting level from the weapon (maximum 4 levels)\nEnable Weapon Preservation to prevent the weapon from breaking on it's last hit\nEnable Weapon Cycling to pull a weapon from input when the current one breaks or is moved to an output\n§cEnchanting the spikes inside the structure does nothing!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nIf the mob spawns §cinfernal§7, it will drain 8 times more power!\nYou can prevent §cinfernal§7 spawns by shift clicking with a screwdriver\nMobs who are always §cinfernal§7 will ignore this factor\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nYou can enable ritual mode with a screwdriver\nWhen in ritual mode, can link to above Well of Suffering rituals\nThe Ritual must be built directly centered above the machine\nWhen linked, mobs will start to buffer and die very slowly, providing blood to the linked altar\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nYou can disable mob animation with a soldering iron\nYou can enable batch mode with wire cutters. Providing §9 16x Time, Output, Weapon Damage\nEnergy Hatch limited by §fGlass§7 Tier, §2§nUV§7-tier unlocks all\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§4§lk§c§lu§6§lb§e§la§2§l6§a§l0§b§l0§3§l0§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.entitycrusher.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §65§7x§67§7x§65§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) §c(Hollow)\n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   35x §r§7Solid Steel Machine Casing (minimum)\n§6   60x §r§7Any Tiered Glass\n§6   20x §r§7Steel Frame Box\n§6   9x §r§7Diamond Spike\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any bottom casing\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Any bottom casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any bottom casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any bottom casing\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.entropic-processor.name=Entropic Processor
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.entropic-processor.tooltip=Machine Type: §eEntropic Processor§r\nProcesses substances by increasing or decreasing their entropy\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHas §68§7 parallels by default\nUsing Advanced Alchemical Constructs increases the machine's parallels to §632§7\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nMixes fluids or solids with a magical catalyst\nCatalyst is consumed by the recipe, then returned upon completion\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nPerforms one perfect overclock per casing tier (Thaumium = 1 perfect OC)\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.entropic-processor.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §67§7x§65§7x§67§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) §c(Hollow)\n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   24x §r§7Warded Glass\n§6   65x§7 - §697x §r§7Alchemically Resistant/Inert/Immune Casing (tiered)\n§6   3x §r§7Alchemical Construct (tiered)\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any Alchemically Resistant/Inert/Immune Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any Alchemically Resistant/Inert/Immune Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any Alchemically Resistant/Inert/Immune Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Any Alchemically Resistant/Inert/Immune Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any Alchemically Resistant/Inert/Immune Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any Alchemically Resistant/Inert/Immune Casing (Hint: 1)\n   Uses sub channel §6casing§r§7 for §6Alchemical Casing Tier\n   Uses sub channel §6construct§r§7 for §6Alchemical Construct Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.exofoundry.name=Exo-Foundry
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.exofoundry.tooltip=Machine Type: §eFluid Solidifier, Foundry§r\n§616§7 Parallels per §fVoltage§7 Tier\n§a150%§7 Speed\n§8100%§7 EU Usage\nWill §lnot§7 perform §doverclocks§7 over the hatch tier without modules\nWill §lnot§7 process §1§nUIV+§7 voltage tier recipes without modules\nHas §63 Tiers§7, depending on Central Chassis Casing\nHas §62/3/4§7 Module Slots, based on machine tier\nEach Module Slot has §67§7 different options\n§6Modules§7 are selected inside the Controller\n§6Module§7 stats are shown in NEI and the Controller\nToggle Render with Screwdriver\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§cGlorious Evolution!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.exofoundry.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §615§7x§655§7x§615§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) §c(Hollow)\n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center, 2nd layer\n§6   462x §r§7Primary Exo-Foundry Casing (minimum)\n§6   548x §r§7Exo-Foundry Containment Glass\n§6   281x §r§7Inner Foundry Siphon Casing\n§6   260x §r§7Central Magnetic Chassis (tiered)\n§6   224x §r§7Netherite Frame Box\n§6   196x §r§7Central Exo-Foundry Regulation Casing\n§6   173x §r§7Black Plutonium Item Pipe Casing\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any Foundry Casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any Foundry Casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any Foundry Casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any Foundry Casing\n   Uses sub channel §6chassis§r§7 for §6Magnetic Chassis Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n   Check NEI for Module structure costs\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.extractor.name=Dissection Apparatus
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.extractor.tooltip=Machine Type: §eExtractor§r\n§68§7 Parallels per §fItem Pipe Casing§7 Tier\n§a300%§7 Speed\n§b85%§7 EU Usage\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.extractor.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §65§7x§65§7x§65§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   45x §r§7Stainless Steel Machine Casing (minimum)\n§6   19x §r§7Item Pipe Casing (tiered)\n§6   8x §r§7Any Tiered Glass\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any Stainless Steel Casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any Stainless Steel Casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any Stainless Steel Casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any Stainless Steel Casing\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   Uses sub channel §6item_pipe§r§7 for §6Item Pipe Casing Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.extremeapiary.name=Industrial Apicultural Acclimatiser and Drone Domestication Station
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.extremeapiary.tooltip=Machine Type: §eMega Apiary, Mapiary§r\nThe ideal home for your bees\nUse screwdriver to change primary mode (INPUT/OUTPUT/OPERATING)\nUse screwdriver + shift to change operation mode (NORMAL/SWARMER)\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§6Input Mode:\n- Does not take power\n- Put your queens in the input bus to put them in the internal buffer\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§6Output Mode:\n- Does not take power\n- Will give your bees back to output bus\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§6Operating Mode:\n- NORMAL:\n  - Processing time: 5 seconds\n  - Uses 1 §dLuV§7 amp per queen\n  - All bees are accelerated 64 times\n  - 8 production upgrades are applied\n  - Genetic Stabilizer upgrade applied\n  - Simulates perfect environment for your bees\n  - Additionally you can provide royal jelly to increase the outputs:\n    - 1 royal jelly grants 5% bonus per bee\n    - They will be consumed on each start of operation\n    - and be applied to that operation only\n    - Max bonus: 200%\n- SWARMER:\n  - You can only insert 1 queen\n  - It will slowly produce ignoble princesses\n  - Consumes 100 royal jelly per operation\n  - Base processing time: 1 minute\n  - Uses 1 amp §9IV§7\n  - Can overclock\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§4§lk§c§lu§6§lb§e§la§2§l6§a§l0§b§l0§3§l0§r§7 & §aRunakai§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.extremeapiary.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §615§7x§617§7x§615§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   190x §r§7Bronze Plated Bricks (minimum)\n§6   121x §r§7Any Tiered Glass\n   The glass tier limits the Energy Input tier\n   Regular water and IC2 Distilled Water are accepted\n§f   Flowers: §7On dirt/grass\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any casing\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.extremedieselengine.name=Extreme Combustion Engine
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.extremedieselengine.tooltip=Machine Type: §eCombustion Generator, ECE§r\n§4DEPRECATED - Controller will be removed in next major update!\n§4Check NEI for new Controller and conversion recipe\nSupply high rating fuel and 8000L of Lubricant per hour to run\nSupply 40L/s of Liquid Oxygen to boost output (optional)\nDefault: Produces 10900EU/t at 100% fuel efficiency\nBoosted: Produces 32700EU/t at 150% fuel efficiency\nYou need to wait for it to reach 300% to output full power\n§53840 §7Pollution per second\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.extremedieselengine.tooltip.15534=Machine Type: §eCombustion Generator, ECE§r\nSupply High Rating Fuels and §f8,000L§7 of Lubricant per hour to run\nSupply §f40L/s§7 of Liquid Oxygen to boost output (optional)\nDefault: Produces §e10,900§f EU/t§7 at §8100%§7 fuel efficiency\nBoosted: Produces §e32,700§f EU/t§7 at §b150%§7 fuel efficiency\nYou need to wait for it to reach §b300%§7 to output full power\nEngine Intake Casings must not be obstructed on top (only air blocks)\n§53840 §7Pollution per second\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nStructure by: §a§6N7Paddy§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.extremedieselengine.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §63§7x§63§7x§64§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   16x§7 - §622x §r§7Robust Tungstensteel Machine Casing\n§f   Titanium Gear Box Machine Casing: §7Inner 2 blocks\n§f   Extreme Engine Intake Machine Casing: §78x, ring around controller\n   Extreme Engine Intake Casings must not be obstructed in front (only air blocks)\n§f   Dynamo Hatch: §7Back center\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7One of the casings next to a Gear Box\n§f   Muffler Hatch: §7Top middle back, above the rear Gear Box\n§f   Input Hatch: §7HOG, next to a Gear Box\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Lubricant, next to a Gear Box\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Liquid Oxygen, optional, next to a Gear Box\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.extremedieselengine.tooltip_secondary.15534=§fDimensions: §610§7x§65§7x§65§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front left, 2nd layer\n§6   30x §r§7Robust Tungstensteel Machine Casing (minimum)\n§6   6x §r§7Steel Gear Box Casing\n§6   12x §r§7Extreme Engine Intake Casing\n§6   32x §r§7PTFE Frame Box\n§6   10x §r§7PTFE Pipe Casing\n§6   4x §r§7Tungstensteel Turbine Casing (minimum)\n§6   12x §r§7Tungstensteel Firebox Casing\n§6   30x §r§7Chemically Inert Machine Casing\n§f   Dynamo Hatch: §7Back center\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any Robust Tungstensteel Machine Casing\n§f   Muffler Hatch: §7Any Robust Tungstensteel Machine Casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7High Rating Fuel, next to a Gear Box\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Lubricant, next to a Gear Box\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Liquid Oxygen, optional, next to a Gear Box\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.extremegreenhouse.name=Extreme Industrial Greenhouse
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.extremegreenhouse.tooltip=Machine Type: §eCrop Farm, EIG§r\nGrow your crops like a chad!\nUse screwdriver to enable/change/disable setup mode\nUse screwdriver while sneaking to enable/disable IC2 mode\nUse wire cutters to give incoming IC2 seeds 0 humidity\nUses 1000L of water per seed per operation\nUses 1L of Weed-EX 9000 per operation per seed if it contains more than 1000 seeds\nOtherwise, around 1% of seeds will be voided each operation\nYou can insert fertilizer each operation to get more drops (max + 400)\nEnergy Hatch limited by §fGlass§7 Tier\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§6Setup Mode:\nDoes not take power\nThere are two modes: input / output\nInput mode: machine will take seeds from input bus and plant them\n[IC2] You need to also input block that is required under the crop\nOutput mode: machine will take planted seeds and output them\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§6Normal Crops:\nMinimal voltage tier: §8EV§7\nStarting with 1 slot\nEvery tier past §8EV§7, slots are multiplied by 2\nEvery slot adds 64 seed to the total seed capacity\nBase process time: 5 sec\nProcess time is divided by number of tiers past §eHV§7 (Minimum 1 sec)\nAll crops are grown at the end of the operation\nDoes not drop seeds\nCan consume up to 2 fertilizer per seed per cycle\nBoost per fertilizer: 200%\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§cDEPRECATED§r\n§6IC2 Crops:\nMinimal voltage tier: §dLuV§7\nMinimal glass tier: §dLuV§7\nStarting with 4 slot\nEvery tier past §dLuV§7, slots are multiplied by 4\nEvery slot adds 1 seed to the total seed capacity\nProcess time: 5 sec\nAll crops are accelerated by x32 times\nCan consume up to 40 fertilizer per seed per cycle\nBoost per fertilizer: 10%\nWeed-EX 9000 consumption is multiplied by 5\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§4§lk§c§lu§6§lb§e§la§2§l6§a§l0§b§l0§3§l0§r§7§r§7; Structure by: §aHydroCN§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.extremegreenhouse.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §67§7x§67§7x§69§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   70x §r§7Sterile Farm Casing (minimum)\n   Tiered glass\n   The glass tier limits the Energy Input tier\n   The dirt is from RandomThings, must be tilled\n   Regular water and IC2 Distilled Water are accepted\n   Purple lamps are from ProjectRedIllumination. They can be powered and/or inverted\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any casing\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any casing\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.fluidextractor.name=Large Fluid Extractor
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.fluidextractor.tooltip=Machine Type: §eFluid Extractor, LFE§r\n§68§7 Parallels per §fSolenoid§7 Tier\n§a150%§7 Speed\n§b80%§7 EU Usage\nEvery coil tier gives a §a+§7§a10%§7 speed bonus and a §b10%§7 EU/t discount (multiplicative)\nThe EU multiplier is §o0.80 * (0.90 ^ Heating Coil Tier)§7, prior to overclocks\nThe energy hatch tier is limited by the glass tier. UEV glass unlocks all tiers\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.fluidextractor.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §65§7x§69§7x§65§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   41x §r§7Robust Tungstensteel Machine Casing (minimum)\n§6   36x §r§7Any Tiered Glass (tiered)\n§6   7x §r§7Solenoid Superconducting Coil (tiered)\n§6   24x §r§7Heating Coils (tiered)\n§6   24x §r§7Black Steel Frame Box\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any Robust Tungstensteel Machine Casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any Robust Tungstensteel Machine Casing\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Any Robust Tungstensteel Machine Casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any Robust Tungstensteel Machine Casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any Robust Tungstensteel Machine Casing\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   Uses sub channel §6coil§r§7 for §6Heating Coils Tier\n   Uses sub channel §6solenoid§r§7 for §6Solenoid Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
