    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.wormhole.name=Miniature Wormhole Generator
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.wormhole.tooltip=Machine Type: §eWormhole Generator, MWG§r\nTransfers EU between two wormhole generators\nWormholes are linked by placing an AE2 Entangled Singularity in each controller slot\nThe transfer rate is limited by the wormhole size, and the wormhole size is governed by the transfer rate\nIf the transfer rate is completely stable, the transfer efficiency is 99.5%\nEU will only be transferred if there is space in the laser source hatch\nEach laser target must have a laser source on the §oother§7 controller, on the §oopposite§7 side\nConsumes an AE2 Singularity from an input bus each time the wormhole is kick-started\nRight click the controller with a screwdriver to disable overclocking\nEnergy Hatch limited by §fGlass§7 Tier\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§9Recursive Pineapple§7, Rendering by: §fBucketBrigade§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.wormhole.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §67§7x§69§7x§67§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   24x §r§7Molecular Casing\n§6   4x §r§7Europium Reinforced Radiation Proof Machine Casing\n§6   22x §r§7Fusion Coil Block\n§6   49x§7 - §653x §r§7High Power Casing\n§6   36x §r§7Any Tiered Glass (tiered)\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7§61§r (Hint Block Number 1)\n§f   Input Bus: §7§61§r (Hint Block Number 1)\n§f   Dynamo Hatch: §7§60§r - §64§r (Laser Only, Hint Block Number 2)\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7§60§r - §64§r (Laser Only, Hint Block Number 2)\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine_dronecentre.name=Drone Centre
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine_dronecentre.tooltip=Machine Type: §eDrone Centre§r\n§bDrone #10032, cleared for takeoff!\nMonitors multiblock machines in range\nReplace maintenance hatch on other multi with drone downlink module\nProvides maintenance, power control, monitoring, and more\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nOperation range is determined by drone tier:\nT1-128, T2-512, T3-4096, T4-4096(Auto)/Infinite(Key)\nT4 drone allows cross-dimension connection!\n§cTo enable cross-dimension,\n§cdownlink module must have the same key with centre.\n§cBut it's not necessary for auto connection in range\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nPlace drones in input bus; only one needed to operate\nAutomatically upgrade based on the drone level in the input bus\nThere is a chance per second that the drone will crash\nChance is determined by drone tier: T1: 1/28800, T2: 1/172800, T3 & T4: 0\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§bSilverMoon§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine_dronecentre.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §65§7x§64§7x§69§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center, 3rd layer\n§6   85x§7 - §691x §r§7Stable Titanium Machine Casing\n§6   8x §r§7Heat Proof Machine Casing\n§6   1x §r§7Robust Tungstensteel Machine Casing\n§6   6x §r§7Any tiered glass\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any Titanium Casing\n   No maintenance hatch needed\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.nag.name=Large Naquadah Reactor
    S:gt.blockmachines.nag.tooltip=Machine Type: §eNaquadah Reactor, LNR§r\nEnvironmentally Friendly!\nGenerate power from high-energy liquids\nConsumes §b2400 L/s Liquid Air§7 to keep running, otherwise§e it will void your fuel§7.\nThe reactor will explode when there is more than§c ONE§7 type of fuel in hatches!\nInput liquid nuclear fuel or liquid naquadah fuel\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nCan increase §defficiency §7by §fconsuming §9coolants:\n§f1000 L/s§7 : §d105% §7: §9IC2 Coolant\n§f1000 L/s§7 : §d150% §7: §9Super Coolant\n§f1000 L/s§7 : §d275% §7: §9Cryotheum\n§f20 L/s§7 : §d500% §7: §9Tachyon Rich Temporal Fluid\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nCan increase §doutput power and fuel usage §7by §fconsuming §cexcited liquid:\n§f180 L/s §7: §d2x power §7: §cMolten Caesium\n§f180 L/s §7: §d3x power §7: §cMolten Uranium-235\n§f20 L/s §7: §d4x power §7: §cMolten Naquadah\n§f20 L/s §7: §d16x power §7: §cMolten Atomic Separation Catalyst\n§f20 L/s §7: §d64x power §7: §cSpatially Enlarged Fluid\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.nag.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §67§7x§68§7x§67§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) §c(Hollow)\n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   48x §r§7Field Restriction Casing\n§6   36x §r§7Radiation Proof Steel Frame Box\n§6   6x §r§7Tungstensteel Pipe Casing\n§6   121x §r§7Radiation Proof Machine Casing\n§f   Dynamo Hatch: §7Any bottom layer casing, only accept ONE!\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any bottom layer casing\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Any bottom layer casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any bottom layer casing\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
