    S:gt.blockmachines.projectmoduleminert1.name=Space Mining Module MK-I
    S:gt.blockmachines.projectmoduleminert1.tooltip=Machine Type: §eSpace Elevator Module§r\nModule that adds Space Mining Operations to the Space Elevator\n§d§lGreat treasures beyond your imagination await!\nDoesn't use an energy hatch, instead receives energy from the Space Elevator\nRequires a plasma to operate (§e825L Helium §7/ §3550L Bismuth §7/ §9375L Radon §7/ §f250L Technetium §7/ §c150L Plutonium 241§7).\nHigher tier plasmas increase the chances of mining bigger asteroids, and improves mining operation time.\nNeeds to be fed with computation to work.\nComputation is consumed per parallel\nMining Drones must be placed in a regular input bus (neither linked nor stocking bus).\nRuns at UV with up to §a2§7 parallels\nNeeds at least §aMotor MK-I§7 to work\nOres can be black-/whitelisted by putting them in an input bus\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.projectmoduleminert1.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §61§7x§65§7x§62§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front, 4th layer\n§6   0x§7 - §69x §r§7Space Elevator Base Casing\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any Space Elevator Base Casing With Hint Number 1\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any Space Elevator Base Casing With Hint Number 1\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any Space Elevator Base Casing With Hint Number 1\n§f   Optical Connector: §7Any Space Elevator Base Casing With Hint Number 1\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
