    S:gt.blockmachines.yottafluidtank.name=YOTTank
    S:gt.blockmachines.yottafluidtank.tooltip=Machine Type: §eFluid Tank§r\nThe max output speed is decided by the amount of stored liquid and the output hatch's capacity\nThe max fluid cell tier is limited by the glass tier\nHV glass for T1, EV glass for T2, IV glass for T3. . .\nThe max height of the cell blocks is 15\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.yottafluidtank.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §65§7x§61-15§7x§65§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center, 2nd layer\n§6   16x §r§7Steel Frame Box\n§6   16x§7 - §6240x §r§7Any Tiered Glass (tiered)\n§6   9x§7 - §6135x §r§7Fluid Cell Block (tiered)\n§6   25x§7 - §643x §r§7YOTTank Casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Hint Block Number 1\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Hint Block Number 3\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.yottafluidtankhatch.name=YOTHatch
    S:gt.blockmachines.yottafluidtankhatch.tooltip=Special I/O port for AE2FC.\nDirectly connected YOTTank with AE fluid storage system.\nUse screwdriver to set storage priority\nUse soldering iron to set read/write mode\nUse wire cutter to enable/disable sticky mode
